Luckily, the couple, who have not been named by police, had a smoke alarm and were woken.

They managed to get the fire under control with an extinguisher before the flames could spread throughout the house.

Despite their heroic efforts, the front door was damaged beyond repair and the walls and ceilings in the hallway were left blackened by the smoke.

Sutton CID say the attack on the morning of November 1 was 'seemingly motiveless attack' and are appealing for witnesses.

